<recipe>
    <name>Lobia Rassedar</name>
    <indexCharacter>L</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Pick, wash lobia several times. Soak in three cups of water for two hours. Drain and boil in three cups of water until three-fourths cooked. Keep aside along with the liquid.

2. Peel, wash and finely chop onions. Wash and chop tomato. Clean, wash and finely chop coriander leaves. Wash and peel ginger. Peel garlic.

3. In a pan heat one tablespoon of oil and add cumin seeds, fenugreek seeds and red chillies. Saute for two minutes on low heat stirring constantly until it emits a fragrant aroma. Let cool and grind with ginger and garlic, using a little water, to a smooth paste.

4. Heat the femaing oil in a saucepan. Add cinnamon and when it begins to sizzle, add onions. Saute until lightly browned.

5. Add tomato, ground paste, turmerice powder, red chillie powder and salt. Cover and let it cook in its own juices for five to seven minutes.

6. Add lobia with water. Cover and cook, until lobia are tender and gravy almost dry.

Chef's tip: You can serve with scraped fresh coconut.</instructions>
